<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,319,1452,1478]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="51">Vararia dussii</emphasis>
Boidin &amp; Lanq.
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1529,1710]" pageId="13" pageNumber="51">
This species is characterized by clamped hyphae, inamyloid, ellipsoid to ovoid basidiospores about 4–6 × 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="51" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 µm</quantity>
, and presence of capillar dichophyses. A species reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[944,1060,1568,1594]" name="Argentina" pageId="13" pageNumber="51">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Boidin, J. &amp; Gilles, G." box="[1076,1335,1568,1594]" pageId="13" pageNumber="51" pagination="115 - 139" refId="ref7831" refString="Boidin, J. &amp; Gilles, G. (1999) Contribution a la conaissance du genre Vararia (Basidiomycotina). Bulletin de la Societe Mycologique de France 115: 115 - 139." type="journal article" year="1999">Boidin &amp; Gilles 1999</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[1357,1431,1568,1594]" name="Brazil" pageId="13" pageNumber="51">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[200,320,1606,1632]" name="Venezuela" pageId="13" pageNumber="51">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hjortstam, K. &amp; Ryvarden, L." box="[336,689,1606,1632]" pageId="13" pageNumber="51" pagination="27 - 146" refId="ref8607" refString="Hjortstam, K. &amp; Ryvarden, L. (2007 a) Checklist of corticioid fungi (Basidiomycotina) from the tropics, subtropics, and the southern hemisphere. Synopsis Fungorum 22: 27 - 146." type="journal article" year="2007">Hjortstam &amp; Ryvarden 2007a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
